The Kano State government has confirmed its first COVID-19 death in the State. A tweet on the official Twitter handle of the Kano State Ministry of Health confirmed the development on Wednesday night. It said, “Wednesday, 15th April 2020. As at 11:55 pm, 1 death of #COVID19 has been recorded in @KanostateNg #StaySafeNigeria.” The State has 21 confirmed cases of the virus. Recall that the State had earlier confirmed 12 new cases of coronavirus. It had said, “Wednesday, 15th April 2020. As at 11:45 pm, 12 additional cases of #COVID19 have been confirmed in @KanostateNg,”